1
00:00:03,110 --> 00:00:04,600
Oh, hey, Joey.

2
00:00:05,740 --> 00:00:08,340
- Hey. - Listen, I need to ask you something.

3
00:00:08,520 --> 00:00:10,770
You know how my stepdad's in prison?

4
00:00:10,820 --> 00:00:12,720
- Yeah. - Yeah.

5
00:00:12,770 --> 00:00:15,580
He was supposed to get a weekend furlough

6
00:00:15,630 --> 00:00:17,380
so he could go to the wedding.

7
00:00:17,430 --> 00:00:19,710
But he just called and....

8
00:00:19,760 --> 00:00:22,600
Well, apparently stabbing lceman in the exercise yard

9
00:00:22,650 --> 00:00:24,470
couldn't wait till Monday.

10
00:00:25,240 --> 00:00:26,880
- So he can't come? - No.

11
00:00:27,360 --> 00:00:28,460
And so there's no one

12
00:00:28,510 --> 00:00:29,570
to walk me down the aisle.

13
00:00:29,620 --> 00:00:30,660
And....

14
00:00:31,410 --> 00:00:33,720
Well, I would just really love it if you would do it.

15
00:00:35,330 --> 00:00:36,760
- Seriously? - Yeah.

16
00:00:36,810 --> 00:00:39,540
You've, you know, sort of been like a dad to me.

17
00:00:41,220 --> 00:00:42,780
I mean, you've always, you know,

18
00:00:42,830 --> 00:00:45,090
looked out for me and shared your wisdom.

19
00:00:47,560 --> 00:00:49,310
I am pretty "wisdomous."

20
00:00:51,260 --> 00:00:53,250
So, what do you say?

21
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:57,400
Are you kidding? Phoebe, I would be honored.

22
00:00:57,980 --> 00:00:59,790
Oh, thank you.

23
00:01:01,670 --> 00:01:03,060
I hope....

24
00:01:04,210 --> 00:01:06,510
I hope you know how much you mean to me.

25
00:01:07,570 --> 00:01:08,990
Listen, I hope....

26
00:01:10,030 --> 00:01:11,690
I hope that you know....

27
00:01:14,430 --> 00:01:15,920
I don't want you to see your father cry.

28
00:01:15,920 --> 00:01:17,270
Go to your room!

29
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:21,620
《老友记》第十季第十二集 菲比的婚礼

30
00:02:09,330 --> 00:02:11,900
Oh, no, no, no. Let your dad get this.

31
00:02:16,570 --> 00:02:17,850
It's my wedding planner.

32
00:02:17,900 --> 00:02:19,860
She's driving me crazy!

33
00:02:20,350 --> 00:02:24,230
Hello? Okay, stop screaming!

34
00:02:25,320 --> 00:02:27,190
Okay, so halibut.

35
00:02:27,970 --> 00:02:29,390
All right, so salmon.

36
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:30,770
Either way. I don't--

37
00:02:30,820 --> 00:02:32,110
It doesn't matter to me.

38
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:33,590
Well, it matters to me!

39
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:38,370
Well, I don't care. So you pick.

40
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:40,150
Did you just hang up on me?

41
00:02:41,930 --> 00:02:42,560
All right, look,

42
00:02:42,610 --> 00:02:43,820
I need you at the rehearsal dinner

43
00:02:43,870 --> 00:02:45,410
tonight at 1800 hours.

44
00:02:45,560 --> 00:02:47,610
Okay. What time is that?

45
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:50,780
You don't know military time?

46
00:02:49,360 --> 00:02:50,780
military time:24小时制

47
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:52,950
I must have been in missile training the day

48
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:53,870
they taught that.

49
00:02:55,410 --> 00:02:56,940
Just subtract 12.

50
00:02:57,380 --> 00:03:00,040
Okay, so 1800 minus 12...

51
00:03:00,090 --> 00:03:02,330
...is 1788.

52
00:03:02,380 --> 00:03:03,780
- Six o'clock! - Okay.

53
00:03:03,950 --> 00:03:06,670
Hold on. Yeah? Geller here.

54
00:03:07,250 --> 00:03:10,000
No, I said it has to be there by 4:00.

55
00:03:10,050 --> 00:03:11,000
Goodbye.

56
00:03:11,730 --> 00:03:13,930
God. How hard is it to make an ice sculpture?

57
00:03:13,930 --> 00:03:16,020
Wait. Ice sculpture? That sounds really fancy.

58
00:03:16,020 --> 00:03:18,100
I told you, I just want a simple wedding.

59
00:03:18,290 --> 00:03:19,800
Please, honey,

60
00:03:19,850 --> 00:03:21,380
leave the details to me.

61
00:03:21,430 --> 00:03:22,360
Now, I wanna make this day

62
00:03:22,410 --> 00:03:24,030
as special for you as I can.

63
00:03:24,080 --> 00:03:26,150
I was thinking the harpist

64
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:26,930
should wear white.

65
00:03:26,980 --> 00:03:27,740
Harpist?

66
00:03:27,790 --> 00:03:30,030
My friend Marjorie is playing the steel drums.

67
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:31,540
Oh, she backed out.

68
00:03:31,590 --> 00:03:32,990
She did? Why?

69
00:03:33,040 --> 00:03:34,180
I made her.

70
00:03:35,170 --> 00:03:37,480
Steel drums don't really say "elegant wedding."

71
00:03:37,530 --> 00:03:39,870
Nor does Marjorie's overwhelming scent.

72
00:03:39,920 --> 00:03:40,660
Hey!

73
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:43,840
She will shower when Tibet is free.

74
00:03:52,490 --> 00:03:56,290
- Hey. You look great. - You too.

75
00:03:56,340 --> 00:03:58,210
I'm glad we're having a rehearsal dinner.

76
00:03:58,260 --> 00:04:00,080
I rarely practice my meals

77
00:04:00,130 --> 00:04:01,470
before I eat.

78
00:04:02,670 --> 00:04:04,910
What did we say was your one gift to us?

79
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:06,400
No stupid jokes,

80
00:04:06,850 --> 00:04:08,690
but I thought that was for the actual wedding.

81
00:04:08,740 --> 00:04:09,930
Rehearse it.

82
00:04:11,190 --> 00:04:12,100
Hi.

83
00:04:12,770 --> 00:04:13,960
Thanks for coming, you guys.

84
00:04:14,010 --> 00:04:15,080
Oh, yeah--

85
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:18,870
I was.... I was going for a handshake.

86
00:04:18,920 --> 00:04:20,870
That why your hand's against my crotch?

87
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:22,410
- That is why. - Yeah.

88
00:04:24,590 --> 00:04:26,150
So, Rach, where's Emma?

89
00:04:26,200 --> 00:04:28,300
Monica made me send her to my mom's.

90
00:04:28,350 --> 00:04:30,990
Apparently, babies and weddings don't mix.

91
00:04:31,620 --> 00:04:34,020
Are you still crying about your damn baby?

92
00:04:35,630 --> 00:04:37,260
Pheebs, you got to keep the line moving.

93
00:04:37,310 --> 00:04:39,350
Remember, 20 seconds per person.

94
00:04:39,400 --> 00:04:41,350
You see these clowns all the time.

95
00:04:45,090 --> 00:04:46,610
Hey, you're Mike's parents, right?

96
00:04:46,610 --> 00:04:47,700
Yes, we are.

97
00:04:48,340 --> 00:04:49,350
Our little ones are

98
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:50,570
growing up fast, aren't they?

99
00:04:52,510 --> 00:04:53,780
- How's that? - You know...

100
00:04:53,830 --> 00:04:55,640
...on one hand, you're happy for them.

101
00:04:55,690 --> 00:04:58,140
On the other, it's hard to let go.

102
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:00,890
Who in God's name are you?

103
00:05:02,060 --> 00:05:03,720
I'm not that fond of you either, buddy.

104
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:05,470
I'm just trying to be nice for the kids.

105
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,020
You know what I realized?

106
00:05:10,070 --> 00:05:12,870
We have no idea what we're doing in the wedding tomorrow.

107
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,610
Yeah, I thought we'd be groomsmen.

108
00:05:14,660 --> 00:05:16,270
They would have asked us by now.

109
00:05:16,320 --> 00:05:18,620
When did they ask you to be a bridesmaid?

110
00:05:19,180 --> 00:05:20,470
November.

111
00:05:20,520 --> 00:05:22,270
I wanna say it's not looking good.

112
00:05:23,420 --> 00:05:24,760
- Hey, Pheebs? - Sorry?

113
00:05:24,810 --> 00:05:26,710
You haven't told these guys

114
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:28,600
what they're doing in the wedding yet.

115
00:05:29,550 --> 00:05:31,650
Well, they're not in the wedding.

116
00:05:31,790 --> 00:05:32,870
What?

117
00:05:37,780 --> 00:05:38,960
Well...

118
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:41,480
...this is really awkward.

119
00:05:42,460 --> 00:05:44,170
Oh, and I can leave.

120
00:05:45,990 --> 00:05:47,380
I'm sorry, you guys.

121
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:49,050
But Mike's got his brother

122
00:05:49,100 --> 00:05:50,590
and his friends from school.

123
00:05:50,640 --> 00:05:52,810
So, you know, you were....

124
00:05:52,860 --> 00:05:53,690
If it helps,

125
00:05:53,740 --> 00:05:54,680
you were next in line.

126
00:05:54,730 --> 00:05:56,550
You just missed the cut.

127
00:05:57,050 --> 00:05:58,420
Oh, man.

128
00:05:58,590 --> 00:06:01,620
This is like figure skating team all over again.

129
00:05:58,590 --> 00:06:08,590
figure skating/synchronized swimming/balance beam:均为女子运动项目

130
00:06:04,700 --> 00:06:06,460
I mean, synchronized swimming.

131
00:06:07,200 --> 00:06:09,810
I mean-- I mean, the balance beam.

132
00:06:10,350 --> 00:06:11,890
- Help me. - Football.

133
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:12,870
Thank you.

134
00:06:14,140 --> 00:06:17,050
Oh, Pheebs, spit that out. That has pork in it.

135
00:06:18,170 --> 00:06:21,000
I thought the pot stickers were supposed to be vegetarian?

136
00:06:21,050 --> 00:06:22,390
Yeah, I changed them.

137
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:24,080
I sent you a fax about it.

138
00:06:24,130 --> 00:06:26,610
I don't have a fax machine.

139
00:06:27,850 --> 00:06:30,390
Well, then there are gonna be a few surprises.

140
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:34,060
I can't believe we're gonna be

141
00:06:34,110 --> 00:06:36,400
the only people that aren't in this wedding.

142
00:06:36,450 --> 00:06:38,260
I know. I hate being left out of things.

143
00:06:38,310 --> 00:06:39,560
And it's a wedding.

144
00:06:39,930 --> 00:06:41,910
It'll be weird if I'm not in it.

145
00:06:43,700 --> 00:06:46,370
- Hey, guys, how's it going? - Fine.

146
00:06:46,420 --> 00:06:48,900
We're sitting here, alone, doing nothing.

147
00:06:48,950 --> 00:06:51,110
It's our rehearsal for tomorrow.

148
00:06:51,990 --> 00:06:54,980
Look, about tomorrow, I've got a question for you.

149
00:06:55,030 --> 00:06:57,040
I found out one of my groomsmen had an emergency

150
00:06:57,090 --> 00:06:58,040
and can't make it.

151
00:06:58,090 --> 00:06:59,020
What happened?

152
00:06:59,070 --> 00:07:00,520
Who cares? And...?

153
00:07:01,850 --> 00:07:04,030
And I was wondering if one of you guys--

154
00:07:04,150 --> 00:07:05,990
- I'll do it! -No... Me!

155
00:07:07,430 --> 00:07:08,470
You both wanna do it?

156
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:10,050
There's only room for one.

157
00:07:10,100 --> 00:07:11,530
Pick me. I look great in a tux,

158
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:12,860
and I won't steal focus.

159
00:07:12,910 --> 00:07:13,800
No, Mike.

160
00:07:13,850 --> 00:07:16,990
No, no, you wanna pick me. I mean.... Watch.

161
00:07:22,470 --> 00:07:24,790
You know, I really don't feel very comfortable

162
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:26,210
making this decision.

163
00:07:26,260 --> 00:07:27,320
You know, Phoebe knows you better.

164
00:07:27,370 --> 00:07:28,570
I'm gonna let her choose.

165
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:32,200
Well, if Phoebe's choosing,

166
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:35,160
then say hello to Mike's next groomsman.

167
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:38,900
Oh, I will. But I will need a mirror...

168
00:07:39,410 --> 00:07:40,780
...as he is me.

169
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:44,360
Please. You're going down.

170
00:07:44,410 --> 00:07:46,060
You are going "downer."

171
00:07:46,110 --> 00:07:48,220
They say that on the figure skating team?

172
00:07:48,270 --> 00:07:50,310
I wouldn't know. I didn't make it.

173
00:07:54,090 --> 00:07:56,570
You know I'm filling in for Phoebe's stepdad tomorrow,

174
00:07:56,620 --> 00:07:57,270
right?

175
00:07:57,320 --> 00:07:58,720
Yeah. Yeah. Hey, thanks for doing that.

176
00:07:58,770 --> 00:08:00,450
Oh, hey, my pleasure.

177
00:08:00,910 --> 00:08:02,790
So, what are your intentions with my Phoebe?

178
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:07,870
- I intend to marry her. - Oh, a wiseacre.

179
00:08:09,300 --> 00:08:11,390
I understand you plan to support your wife

180
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:13,690
by playing the piano?

181
00:08:14,730 --> 00:08:16,400
Isn't that kind of unstable?

182
00:08:17,140 --> 00:08:19,740
- No more so than acting. - Strike two.

183
00:08:20,860 --> 00:08:24,310
You're right. She probably will support me.

184
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,620
Hey, unless we move in with you, Dad.

185
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:29,480
Strike three.

186
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:32,510
You only get one more, Mike.

187
00:08:35,640 --> 00:08:38,520
So? What did you decide?

188
00:08:38,860 --> 00:08:40,510
I decided to pee.

189
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,070
He didn't tell you?

190
00:08:43,120 --> 00:08:44,320
You have to choose one of us

191
00:08:44,370 --> 00:08:45,180
to be in your wedding.

192
00:08:45,230 --> 00:08:46,460
One of the groomsmen fell out.

193
00:08:46,510 --> 00:08:47,590
Oh, no, no.

194
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:49,600
I can't choose between you two.

195
00:08:49,650 --> 00:08:51,240
I love you both so much.

196
00:08:51,290 --> 00:08:53,120
Just not enough to put us in

197
00:08:53,170 --> 00:08:55,080
the original wedding party.

198
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:57,550
But I don't wanna choose. It's....

199
00:08:58,000 --> 00:08:59,710
Okay, wait. Rach?

200
00:08:59,710 --> 00:09:03,820
Listen, I have a very special bridesmaid task for you to do.

201
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:05,700
Goody! What is it?

202
00:09:05,930 --> 00:09:08,520
Well, there's a spot open for only one groomsman...

203
00:09:08,570 --> 00:09:10,630
...and you have to choose between Ross and Chandler.

204
00:09:10,680 --> 00:09:11,800
So good luck with that.

205
00:09:12,370 --> 00:09:13,300
What? What, what, what?

206
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:14,980
No, I don't wanna do that.

207
00:09:15,030 --> 00:09:16,800
All right. I guess I have to find a new bridesmaid.

208
00:09:16,800 --> 00:09:17,910
I'll do it!

209
00:09:19,230 --> 00:09:21,490
Okay, it's 2100 hours.

210
00:09:21,540 --> 00:09:22,580
Time for your toast.

211
00:09:22,630 --> 00:09:24,420
Do I have time to go to the bathroom?

212
00:09:24,470 --> 00:09:26,370
You had a bathroom break at 2030.

213
00:09:26,420 --> 00:09:28,250
Pee on your own time, Mike.

214
00:09:31,030 --> 00:09:32,680
In regards to the toasts, okay,

215
00:09:32,730 --> 00:09:34,140
you wanna keep them short.

216
00:09:34,190 --> 00:09:35,440
Nothing kills a rehearsal dinner

217
00:09:35,490 --> 00:09:37,260
like long speeches. Okay.

218
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:39,650
You just get in, do your thing, and get out.

219
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:41,230
Is that what you say to Chandler?

220
00:09:43,340 --> 00:09:44,820
It's 2101,

221
00:09:44,870 --> 00:09:46,070
and I am not amused.

222
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:48,490
Okay.

223
00:09:49,300 --> 00:09:52,450
The bride and groom have a few words they'd like to say.

224
00:09:54,950 --> 00:09:57,080
Okay. Hello, everyone.

225
00:09:57,130 --> 00:09:59,520
And thank you all for being here tonight.

226
00:09:59,570 --> 00:10:01,520
So tomorrow's the big event.

227
00:10:01,840 --> 00:10:03,030
Some of you might not know,

228
00:10:03,080 --> 00:10:05,920
but Mike and I didn't get off to the best start.

229
00:10:05,970 --> 00:10:09,580
Yeah. My friend Joey and l...

230
00:10:09,630 --> 00:10:13,930
...decided to fix each other up with friends. So l--

231
00:10:16,140 --> 00:10:17,980
Oh, okay. I....

232
00:10:18,780 --> 00:10:20,250
I gave it a lot of thought,

233
00:10:20,300 --> 00:10:22,500
and I fixed him up with my friend Mary Ellen...

234
00:10:22,550 --> 00:10:25,750
...who couldn't be here tonight, because.... It's not--

235
00:10:26,170 --> 00:10:28,470
It's not important. Well, she's in rehab.

236
00:10:29,350 --> 00:10:30,300
Anyway.

237
00:10:30,350 --> 00:10:33,980
So Joey said that he was fixing me up with his friend Mike...

238
00:10:34,030 --> 00:10:35,660
...only he didn't have a friend Mike,

239
00:10:35,710 --> 00:10:37,780
so he just brought my Mike.

240
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:39,770
And-- And--

241
00:10:40,570 --> 00:10:43,960
But despite, you know-- It got good.

242
00:10:45,510 --> 00:10:47,100
Ok, I wanna take a moment

243
00:10:47,150 --> 00:10:48,290
to mention my mother,

244
00:10:48,340 --> 00:10:49,420
who couldn't be here.

245
00:10:49,470 --> 00:10:50,660
Oh, God.

246
00:10:51,340 --> 00:10:53,420
And.... And moment's over.

247
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:56,560
So okay.... Oh, no, forget that.

248
00:10:56,730 --> 00:10:59,140
I can forget that. Oh, this is funny.

249
00:10:59,190 --> 00:11:02,940
Oh, but you need to know that to get that.

250
00:11:02,990 --> 00:11:05,410
So.... Oh, well, okay.

251
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:08,030
I.... Okay.

252
00:11:08,610 --> 00:11:11,020
Okay, Monica, I can't do it like this!

253
00:11:12,270 --> 00:11:14,510
This is my wedding, okay?

254
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:16,350
I don't want this--

255
00:11:16,400 --> 00:11:18,910
Or this-- Or this--

256
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:21,270
Okay? I just wanted a simple wedding...

257
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:23,090
...where my fiance can go to the bathroom

258
00:11:23,090 --> 00:11:24,670
any time he wants!

259
00:11:28,190 --> 00:11:30,470
- You know what? You're done. - What?

260
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:31,830
You're fired!

261
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:34,880
Cheers.

262
00:11:45,480 --> 00:11:47,180
- Hey. - Happy wedding day.

263
00:11:47,230 --> 00:11:48,910
Happy my wedding day to you.

264
00:11:50,140 --> 00:11:51,260
Joey, listen,

265
00:11:51,310 --> 00:11:52,540
this is gonna be bridesmaid central,

266
00:11:52,590 --> 00:11:53,100
all right?

267
00:11:53,150 --> 00:11:54,240
We're gonna have hair and makeup

268
00:11:54,290 --> 00:11:55,350
in the bathroom.

269
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:57,260
I had to move a couple things in the fridge

270
00:11:57,310 --> 00:11:58,850
to make room for the corsages.

271
00:11:58,900 --> 00:12:01,270
因为瑞秋说要把corsage放到冰箱里  乔伊以为可以吃

272
00:11:58,900 --> 00:12:01,270
Man! I wouldn't have had breakfast

273
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:03,330
if I knew there was gonna be corsages.

274
00:12:07,060 --> 00:12:07,880
Hi.

275
00:12:09,710 --> 00:12:11,200
About last night....

276
00:12:12,110 --> 00:12:14,630
I know you're under a lot of stress, and....

277
00:12:14,790 --> 00:12:18,040
Well, even though the things you said

278
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:19,840
...as someone who's never been fired before--

279
00:12:20,550 --> 00:12:22,490
My point is....

280
00:12:22,490 --> 00:12:25,180
Well, I'm willing to take my job back.

281
00:12:26,460 --> 00:12:28,080
Oh, well, that's okay.

282
00:12:29,510 --> 00:12:31,420
I think you and I will do much better

283
00:12:31,470 --> 00:12:33,560
if you're just here as a bridesmaid.

284
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:37,030
Is that so?

285
00:12:37,870 --> 00:12:38,900
Okay.

286
00:12:39,330 --> 00:12:40,490
If that's really what you want,

287
00:12:40,540 --> 00:12:41,560
then here.

288
00:12:41,680 --> 00:12:43,260
I give you the headset.

289
00:12:43,310 --> 00:12:45,160
I don't really wanna give you the headset.

290
00:12:46,450 --> 00:12:47,690
I guess if you're taking over,

291
00:12:47,740 --> 00:12:50,830
then you should probably return these messages.

292
00:12:50,880 --> 00:12:52,360
Wow. This is a lot.

293
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:54,890
But I'm sure you can handle this.

294
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:56,260
I have won awards...

295
00:12:56,310 --> 00:12:57,910
...for my organizational skills.

296
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:59,370
But I'm sure you'll do fine.

297
00:12:59,630 --> 00:13:00,690
You've won awards?

298
00:13:00,740 --> 00:13:02,770
I printed them out on my computer.

299
00:13:05,150 --> 00:13:06,380
- Hey. - Hi.

300
00:13:06,430 --> 00:13:07,560
Where's Rach?

301
00:13:07,610 --> 00:13:08,790
She's in her room. Why?

302
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:09,800
I have to talk to her about

303
00:13:09,810 --> 00:13:11,250
this groomsman situation.

304
00:13:11,300 --> 00:13:13,150
Ok, I'm not gonna watch Chandler up there

305
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:15,210
while I'm in the seats like some chump.

306
00:13:20,250 --> 00:13:23,370
My God, you're breathtaking.

307
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:27,290
What do you want?

308
00:13:28,460 --> 00:13:29,670
You haven't by any chance

309
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:31,950
chosen a groomsman yet, have you?

310
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:32,780
Ross,

311
00:13:32,830 --> 00:13:34,880
please don't make this harder than it already is.

312
00:13:34,930 --> 00:13:35,840
I'm not.

313
00:13:35,890 --> 00:13:37,880
I'm making it easier. Pick me.

314
00:13:38,990 --> 00:13:41,110
Chandler said it's important to him too.

315
00:13:41,110 --> 00:13:42,550
Listen. Listen.

316
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:43,990
Whoever you pick

317
00:13:44,040 --> 00:13:45,980
is gonna walk down the aisle with you.

318
00:13:46,150 --> 00:13:48,830
Now, I promise I won't say a word.

319
00:13:48,880 --> 00:13:50,200
But if you pick Chandler...

320
00:13:50,250 --> 00:13:51,710
...he's gonna be whispering stupid jokes

321
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:53,230
in your ear the whole time.

322
00:13:54,350 --> 00:13:56,580
Oh, you are the lesser of two evils.

323
00:13:56,580 --> 00:13:57,780
Yes!

324
00:14:03,770 --> 00:14:05,860
Sven, I don't understand what you're saying.

325
00:14:05,920 --> 00:14:07,730
What is wrong with the flowers?

326
00:14:07,940 --> 00:14:10,240
"Lorkins"? What the hell are "lorkins"?

327
00:14:10,290 --> 00:14:11,360
I know.

328
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:13,820
Hey.

329
00:14:13,870 --> 00:14:15,410
Mike, if you were Swedish...

330
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:18,680
...and you were saying the word "lorkins," what flower would that be?

331
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:20,440
Orchids?

332
00:14:20,490 --> 00:14:21,160
Right there!

333
00:14:21,210 --> 00:14:23,100
That's why I'm marrying you.

334
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:32,140
Hello, Michael.

335
00:14:33,470 --> 00:14:34,600
Joseph.

336
00:14:36,840 --> 00:14:38,280
May I have a word with you, please?

337
00:14:49,220 --> 00:14:50,510
This is...

338
00:14:51,280 --> 00:14:52,420
...great.

339
00:14:53,390 --> 00:14:54,670
Have a seat.

340
00:14:58,070 --> 00:14:59,530
Last night...

341
00:15:00,920 --> 00:15:04,240
...l tried to welcome you into my family.

342
00:15:06,370 --> 00:15:09,620
And instead, you disrespect me.

343
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:11,820
I cannot allow this.

344
00:15:13,060 --> 00:15:15,970
Are you rehearsing for some really bad Mafia movie?

345
00:15:17,110 --> 00:15:18,710
More back talk.

346
00:15:19,480 --> 00:15:20,600
And yes,

347
00:15:20,650 --> 00:15:22,550
I may be borrowing a few lines

348
00:15:22,600 --> 00:15:25,120
from my recent unsuccessful audition...

349
00:15:25,170 --> 00:15:26,560
...for <i>Family Honor 2:</i>

350
00:15:26,610 --> 00:15:28,330
<i>This A-Time It's A-Personal.</i>

351
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:33,200
Joey, I kind of have a lot to do today.

352
00:15:33,250 --> 00:15:34,010
What do you want?

353
00:15:34,060 --> 00:15:35,880
I want you to take this seriously!

354
00:15:36,140 --> 00:15:37,420
Phoebe is very,

355
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:39,740
very important to me, okay?

356
00:15:39,790 --> 00:15:40,560
I wanna make sure

357
00:15:40,610 --> 00:15:41,890
you are gonna take care of her.

358
00:15:43,920 --> 00:15:45,890
Joe, I love Phoebe.

359
00:15:46,350 --> 00:15:48,550
She's the most important thing in my life.

360
00:15:48,600 --> 00:15:50,900
I'd die before I let anything happen to her.

361
00:15:53,250 --> 00:15:55,760
That's what I wanted to hear.

362
00:15:56,730 --> 00:15:59,370
Because she's family, okay?

363
00:15:59,420 --> 00:16:01,110
And now you're gonna be family.

364
00:16:01,640 --> 00:16:03,040
And there's nothing more important

365
00:16:03,090 --> 00:16:05,830
in the whole world than family.

366
00:16:07,010 --> 00:16:08,920
That must have been one lousy movie.

367
00:16:08,970 --> 00:16:10,500
That was me!

368
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:15,250
Hi.

369
00:16:15,300 --> 00:16:16,730
Let's talk about this groomsman thing.

370
00:16:16,780 --> 00:16:18,040
If you pick Ross,

371
00:16:18,090 --> 00:16:20,070
he'll walk you down the aisle just fine.

372
00:16:20,120 --> 00:16:21,800
But if you choose me...

373
00:16:22,350 --> 00:16:24,210
...you'll be getting some comedy.

374
00:16:26,850 --> 00:16:28,950
Even so...

375
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:34,400
...l think I'm gonna pick Ross.

376
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:36,630
Let me tell you why you need to pick me.

377
00:16:38,860 --> 00:16:40,440
See, when I was a kid, you know,

378
00:16:40,490 --> 00:16:43,170
I was always left out of everything...

379
00:16:43,170 --> 00:16:46,840
You know... and it really made me feel insecure.

380
00:16:46,890 --> 00:16:50,730
I was always picked last in gym...

381
00:16:51,340 --> 00:16:53,210
...even behind that fat exchange student

382
00:16:53,210 --> 00:16:55,440
who didn't know the rules to baseball.

383
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:57,140
I mean, this guy would strike out

384
00:16:57,140 --> 00:16:58,810
and then run to third.

385
00:17:01,210 --> 00:17:03,370
Anyway, if I'm the only one

386
00:17:03,370 --> 00:17:04,540
left out of this wedding...

387
00:17:04,540 --> 00:17:06,060
...l just know that all those feelings

388
00:17:06,060 --> 00:17:08,400
are gonna come rushing back.

389
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:12,970
All right, fine, I pick you.

390
00:17:13,020 --> 00:17:14,260
Yes!

391
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:18,590
Make "groom" for Chandler.

392
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:18,590
groom与room谐音 钱德勒做了"伴郎"亦即有了"一席之地"

393
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:23,760
Oh, my.

394
00:17:25,440 --> 00:17:27,860
No, we're gonna do it my way.

395
00:17:27,910 --> 00:17:30,100
Because your way is stupid.

396
00:17:30,300 --> 00:17:31,730
All right, I got to go.

397
00:17:31,780 --> 00:17:33,400
I have another call, Reverend.

398
00:17:35,160 --> 00:17:36,410
Hello?

399
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:38,360
I'm glad we had this little talk.

400
00:17:38,410 --> 00:17:39,090
Yes.

401
00:17:39,270 --> 00:17:41,860
And thanks for all the wedding night advice.

402
00:17:42,360 --> 00:17:44,480
That didn't make me uncomfortable at all.

403
00:17:45,220 --> 00:17:47,450
All right, so I'll see everybody tonight.

404
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:48,930
- Okay. - Bye.

405
00:17:53,380 --> 00:17:54,390
Did you guys know that

406
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:56,870
there's a giant ice sculpture in the hall?

407
00:17:57,220 --> 00:17:59,460
Oh, my God, what's it doing here?

408
00:17:59,510 --> 00:18:01,460
I guess it got sent to the billing address

409
00:18:01,510 --> 00:18:03,320
as opposed to the shipping address.

410
00:18:03,670 --> 00:18:04,910
What a pickle.

411
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:08,110
Oh, my God, everything's such a mess.

412
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:10,210
Why is this happening to me?

413
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:13,640
How bad do you wanna stick your tongue on that?

414
00:18:20,630 --> 00:18:23,030
- How's it going? - Good.

415
00:18:23,230 --> 00:18:25,240
I'm just getting some coffee

416
00:18:25,290 --> 00:18:27,470
so I'm alert for the wedding.

417
00:18:28,360 --> 00:18:30,790
That's what I was doing too.

418
00:18:31,400 --> 00:18:34,450
Well, you have fun tonight.

419
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:36,710
- You too. - Oh, I will.

420
00:18:37,650 --> 00:18:38,900
Me too.

421
00:18:43,180 --> 00:18:43,980
Wait a minute.

422
00:18:44,030 --> 00:18:45,770
I know why I'm being such an ass.

423
00:18:45,820 --> 00:18:46,850
Why are you?

424
00:18:47,940 --> 00:18:49,620
I'm not supposed to tell you.

425
00:18:49,670 --> 00:18:51,360
I'm not supposed to tell you.

426
00:18:51,980 --> 00:18:54,320
You told us both we could be in the wedding?

427
00:18:56,160 --> 00:18:57,450
In my defense,

428
00:18:57,500 --> 00:18:59,590
you weren't supposed to tell each other!

429
00:19:00,600 --> 00:19:02,250
Rachel, only one of us can do it.

430
00:19:02,300 --> 00:19:03,290
You have to choose.

431
00:19:03,340 --> 00:19:05,840
You and me together again.

432
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,120
Rach, Rach?

433
00:19:08,170 --> 00:19:09,110
Knock-knock.

434
00:19:09,160 --> 00:19:11,470
- Who's there? - I'll tell you at the wedding.

435
00:19:12,380 --> 00:19:14,130
Hey, I forgot my scarf.

436
00:19:14,620 --> 00:19:15,890
You know what. I can't do this.

437
00:19:15,940 --> 00:19:17,850
I don't know which one of you guys to pick.

438
00:19:17,900 --> 00:19:19,100
Oh, you haven't picked yet?

439
00:19:19,210 --> 00:19:20,990
Oh, good, because I had an idea.

440
00:19:21,040 --> 00:19:22,320
I thought it would be fun

441
00:19:22,370 --> 00:19:25,410
if the third groomsman was my family dog, Chappy.

442
00:19:26,070 --> 00:19:27,310
What? A dog?

443
00:19:27,360 --> 00:19:29,580
No. Rachel gets to choose.

444
00:19:30,390 --> 00:19:32,540
Wow, this is a tough one.

445
00:19:33,280 --> 00:19:35,250
I think I'm gonna have to go with the dog.

446
00:19:36,490 --> 00:19:38,360
So, what you're saying is that

447
00:19:38,410 --> 00:19:40,520
the chef is at the Hamilton Club...

448
00:19:40,570 --> 00:19:41,690
...but the food is not?

449
00:19:41,740 --> 00:19:42,970
And the drinks are there

450
00:19:43,020 --> 00:19:44,740
but the bartender is not?

451
00:19:44,790 --> 00:19:47,490
Are you freaking kidding me?

452
00:19:48,710 --> 00:19:49,900
How's it going?

453
00:19:50,720 --> 00:19:52,360
- Help me. - What?

454
00:19:52,410 --> 00:19:54,940
I want you to be crazy bitch again.

455
00:19:57,430 --> 00:19:58,620
Really?

456
00:19:59,850 --> 00:20:00,910
Please?

457
00:20:01,890 --> 00:20:03,740
You really want me to come back?

458
00:20:03,790 --> 00:20:05,790
More than I wanna get married.

459
00:20:08,360 --> 00:20:11,020
Okay, people, we are back in business!

460
00:20:11,810 --> 00:20:14,880
Oh, God, I have missed you so much. Okay.

461
00:20:14,930 --> 00:20:17,110
Ok. Get your hair and makeup done.

462
00:20:17,160 --> 00:20:18,590
I'll take care of everything.

463
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:20,260
Hey, what are you guys gonna do?

464
00:20:20,310 --> 00:20:21,110
About what?

465
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:23,770
The blizzard. I just saw on the news...

466
00:20:23,820 --> 00:20:25,670
...it's the worst snowstorm in 20 years.

467
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:27,920
They already closed all the bridges and tunnels.

468
00:20:29,510 --> 00:20:30,980
But the band and the photographer

469
00:20:31,030 --> 00:20:32,930
are coming in from New Jersey.

470
00:20:32,980 --> 00:20:34,360
I don't think they are.

471
00:20:35,440 --> 00:20:36,740
Looks like you're not gonna

472
00:20:36,790 --> 00:20:38,360
be in the wedding, either.

473
00:20:40,230 --> 00:20:41,780
So sorry, Pheebs.

474
00:20:53,820 --> 00:20:55,770
Well, the club lost its power.

475
00:20:55,820 --> 00:20:57,970
Yeah according to the news, most of the city did.

476
00:20:58,020 --> 00:20:59,850
Since when do you watch the news?

477
00:20:59,900 --> 00:21:01,350
For your information...

478
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:03,990
...since they hired a very hot weather girl.

479
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:06,670
I can't believe

480
00:21:06,720 --> 00:21:08,430
you aren't getting married today.

481
00:21:08,480 --> 00:21:09,350
I know.

482
00:21:09,900 --> 00:21:12,600
Wow, you know, it's so beautiful out there.

483
00:21:12,650 --> 00:21:14,470
You always wanted to get married outside.

484
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:16,260
Why don't you just do it on the street?

485
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:17,170
What?

486
00:21:17,220 --> 00:21:19,590
Well, look, it's hardly snowing anymore.

487
00:21:20,030 --> 00:21:23,360
I mean, you couldn't ask for a more romantic setting.

488
00:21:23,410 --> 00:21:24,680
This could be the simple wedding

489
00:21:24,730 --> 00:21:26,160
you've always wanted.

490
00:21:27,200 --> 00:21:28,490
What do you think?

491
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:32,520
I think I wanna get married to you today.

492
00:21:34,820 --> 00:21:38,190
Me too. Monica, do you think we could do it?

493
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:41,660
Affirmative!

494
00:21:49,590 --> 00:21:52,020
Okay, let's get these chairs out here!

495
00:21:52,070 --> 00:21:54,470
Gunther, hit the Christmas lights.

496
00:22:01,440 --> 00:22:04,770
Okay, who left the ice sculpture

497
00:22:04,820 --> 00:22:06,610
on the steam grate?

498
00:22:08,250 --> 00:22:09,410
Michael.

499
00:22:09,460 --> 00:22:12,330
Hey, you made it. Great. Chappy!

500
00:22:12,380 --> 00:22:15,670
- There you go. - Hi. Hi.

501
00:22:16,390 --> 00:22:18,160
Mom, I know getting married in the street isn't

502
00:22:18,210 --> 00:22:19,460
what you approve of.

503
00:22:19,510 --> 00:22:21,160
No, it's lovely.

504
00:22:21,210 --> 00:22:23,170
The lights and the snow.

505
00:22:23,220 --> 00:22:25,100
I could look at them forever.

506
00:22:25,150 --> 00:22:27,380
I crushed a pill and put it in her drink.

507
00:22:28,390 --> 00:22:30,130
Come on, sweetheart.

508
00:22:32,060 --> 00:22:33,460
You know, Chappy's too small

509
00:22:33,510 --> 00:22:34,830
to handle all this snow.

510
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:36,770
Someone has to walk him down the aisle.

511
00:22:36,820 --> 00:22:38,630
Would this person be in the wedding?

512
00:22:38,680 --> 00:22:39,390
I guess.

513
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:40,650
- I'll do it! - I'll do it!

514
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:42,730
Chandler, hello?

515
00:22:42,780 --> 00:22:44,970
I mean, aren't you scared of dogs?

516
00:22:45,020 --> 00:22:46,230
I'm not scared.

517
00:22:46,280 --> 00:22:48,030
I'll just take little Chappy and--

518
00:22:48,080 --> 00:22:48,980
He can sense my fear!

519
00:22:49,030 --> 00:22:50,250
My throat is exposed!

520
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:55,100
I guess I'm in the wedding then.

521
00:22:56,550 --> 00:22:58,070
He stinks.

522
00:22:59,070 --> 00:23:00,150
Level one alert!

523
00:23:00,200 --> 00:23:02,670
I repeat, level one, this is not a drill!

524
00:23:02,720 --> 00:23:04,110
We have a situation.

525
00:23:04,160 --> 00:23:04,900
The minister called.

526
00:23:04,950 --> 00:23:06,260
He's snowed in, he can't make it.

527
00:23:06,310 --> 00:23:08,180
- Oh, no. - Hey, don't worry.

528
00:23:08,230 --> 00:23:09,970
I'm still ordained from your wedding.

529
00:23:10,020 --> 00:23:10,710
Really?

530
00:23:10,760 --> 00:23:12,640
Yeah. You think I'd give up being a minister

531
00:23:12,690 --> 00:23:14,590
and pay to ride the subway?

532
00:23:15,430 --> 00:23:18,310
Ministers don't ride the subway for free.

533
00:23:18,360 --> 00:23:19,960
I had to read the Bible pretty carefully,

534
00:23:20,010 --> 00:23:21,850
but, yeah, we do.

535
00:23:22,690 --> 00:23:24,300
Ok, if Joey does the ceremony,

536
00:23:24,350 --> 00:23:26,150
then we have to find someone else to walk Phoebe down the aisle.

537
00:23:26,200 --> 00:23:27,310
I'll do it!

538
00:23:32,050 --> 00:23:34,330
Okay, Mike and Joey, get in position.

539
00:23:34,380 --> 00:23:35,840
Chandler, come with me.

540
00:23:42,220 --> 00:23:44,880
Okay, Joey's doing the ceremony,

541
00:23:44,930 --> 00:23:46,480
and Chandler's giving you away.

542
00:23:46,650 --> 00:23:49,310
Oh, okay. Hi, new Dad.

543
00:23:51,250 --> 00:23:54,050
So you ready to do this?

544
00:23:54,830 --> 00:23:57,040
Oh, my God. This is really happening.

545
00:23:57,700 --> 00:24:00,690
